er (  1102–67 ) of  Henry I  of England; she was married early in life to the Holy Roman Emperor  Henry V , and later disputed the throne of England with her cousin  Stephen . In  1128  she married  Geoffrey , Count of Anjou. A medieval chronicler commented, ‘she was a good woman, but she had little bliss with him’. The name <i>Maud</i> became quite common in England in the 19th century, when its popularity was influenced in part by  Tennyson's  poem Maud, published in  1855 , but has not been much used since the early decades of the 20th century."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Maud was born about 1265. She had at least 1 daughter with John Comyn. She died after 1331, in Ulceby, Lincolnshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"Abt 1265–after 1331":"umbes 1265–pärast 1331","1270–1332":"1270–1332","1310–1360":"1310–1360","1265–1331":"1265–1331","Abt 1310":"umbes 1310","Abt 1265":"umbes 1265","1332":"1332","1310":"1310","1331":"1331","1265":"1265","1360":"1360","after 1331":"pärast 1331","1270":"1270","Scotland":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England","Ulceby, Lincolnshire. England":"Ulceby, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1265–after 1331":"noin 1265–1331 jälkeen","1270–1332":"1270–1332","1310–1360":"1310–1360","1265–1331":"1265–1331","Abt 1310":"noin 1310","Abt 1265":"noin 1265","1332":"1332","1310":"1310","1331":"1331","1265":"1265","1360":"1360","after 1331":"1331 jälkeen","1270":"1270","Scotland":"Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Lincolnshire, England":"Lincolnshire, England","Ulceby, Lincolnshire. England":"Ulceby, Lincolnshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1265–after 1331":"environ 1265–après 1331","1270–1332":"1270–1332","1310–1360":"1310–1360","1265–1331":"1265–1331","Abt 1310":"environ 1310","Abt 1265":"environ 1265","1332":"1332","1310":"1310","1331":"1331","1265":"1265","1360":"1360","after 1331":"après 1331","1270":"1270","Scotland":"Écosse, Royaume-Uni","Lincolnshire, England":